### **3. Short Rhyming Poem:**
**"The Tiger of the Mind"**

We call it pain, we call it dread,
A shadow cast by thoughts we’ve fed.
Yet God’s the hand that spins the thread—
So why not choose what we have said?

The tiger’s teeth? A doll’s disguise,
A fear we built with trembling eyes.
Move through the dark, or shift the skies—
The world you see is yours to rise. [end of text]


